  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: iGeth/v1.7.0-stable/darwin-arm64/go1.7.1\r\nOS & Version: iOS\r\nCommit hash : iOS 11.0.1\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nExpecting that the getBalanceAt method of GethEthereumClient returns the balance in Wei\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nAlways returns 0, even when all blocks have been synced.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n````\r\n// Set up Geth\r\nlet config = GethNewNodeConfig()!\r\nconfig.setEthereumNetworkID(1) // Homestead Main Network\r\nvar error: NSError?\r\nlet gethNode = try! GethNewNode(NSSearchPathForDirectoriesInDomains(.documentDirectory, .userDomainMask, true).first!, config, &error)\r\ntry! gethNode.start()\r\nlet gethClient = try! gethNode.getEthereumClient()\r\n\r\n// Confirm that all blocks have been synced\r\nlet block = try! gethClient.getBlockByNumber(GethNewContext(), number:-1)\r\nprint(\"Latest block: \\(block.getNumber())\") // \"Latest block: 4332263\"\r\n        \r\n// Find balance of random ETH address (not mine) with 0.215430389 ETH.\r\nvar error: NSError?\r\nlet address = GethNewAddressFromHex(\"0x3914bff975ef35e8d3403e1ea953bf886b0e8fea\", &error)\r\nlet balance = try! gethClient.getBalanceAt(GethNewContext(), account: address!, number: 0)\r\nprint(\"Balance: \\(balance.getInt64())\") // \"Balance: 0\" Expected: 215430389 (Wei)\r\n````\r\n",
