    "body": "`let balance = try! gethClient.getBalanceAt(GethNewContext(), account: address!, number: 0)`\r\n\r\nwith number:0 you are asking for the balance at block 0 - so the balance is 0.\r\n\r\nThis is how I do it with WALLETH on android:\r\n\r\n```\r\nethereumNode.ethereumClient.subscribeNewHead(ethereumContext, object : NewHeadHandler {\r\n     override fun onNewHead(head: Header) {\r\n         val address = keyStore.getCurrentAddress().toGethAddr()\r\n         val balance = ethereumNode.ethereumClient.getBalanceAt(ethereumContext, address, head.number)\r\n         ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nAFAIR you can also pass in -1 for the latest block - but you can also use the block-number you got via:\r\n`let block = try! gethClient.getBlockByNumber(GethNewContext(), number:-1)`",
